<br>
When I played a warrior, he was an ogre and thus just used slam.  I was damn irked when kick-stun was added to the game -- dilutes pretty much the only large race advantage, though unstunnable for ogres is still nice.  Now that it's here, if you have kick-stun, just use that.  If you don't, work up your bash.  It's really nice and for some raid fights (the push/bash fights).  All your bashers must have a high bash or kick skill for those fights. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=asotus007>Asotus007</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 277<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(3/24/03 3:24 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm43.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=212.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Ghetto bash?</span><hr size=1> Sar, the endgame evolution of warriors is not duel-wielding. It is two-handed weapons and/or an EB weapon and a furious bash shield. Keep bash maxed.<br>
