<br>
Bash and slam use the same timer, once you get bash, slam will raise your skill caps in bashing.<br>
<br>
Saurix gave the best way to set up hotkeys to minimise mouse work, so i cant add on that.<br>
<br>
You can use ogre/troll/barbarian potions and slam if you put some points in bash in 'theory' it should move - however it means you get to look like a ogre/troll/barbarian for the duration.<br>
<br>
I developed my skills and picked 2h bash - wich is fun, but most creatures in pop are very hard to interupt with a spell.<br>
<br>
Kunark - Sebilis frogs, bash works a treat here.<br>
<br>
Velious - Giants - pain to bash, interupts a bit, bash is <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Great<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong> For push, basicaly a full bash will give you a sound effect so you can tell if it passed (with shield equiped) it will usualy knockback the mob hence helping push. I loved my shield in veliouse days because it increased the push rate i could generate.<br>
<br>
Luclin - rarely get a bash interupt to work.<br>
<br>
PoP - Almost never get bash interupt to work.<br>
<br>
Most of that is probably because of knights cap in bash, wich is lower than warriors and also the things we fight vs our skill caps.<br>
<br>
It's a pain to raise bash, it's one of those skills that just takes a while to work up, but it's not a bad skill - i dont have kick but it's still quite fun. I miss the old bash animations, it looked so great when you shield plunked somone round the head with it. *makes shield plunk noise*<br>
