<br>
2h bash - allows you to bash while useing a two handed blunt, slashing and piercing wepon.<br>
2h bash uses the Bash skill.<br>
<br>
Bash - allows you to bash an enemy while wielding a shield in your secondary hand, bash will disable kick &amp; slam and a rogue said even disables his backstab.<br>
<br>
Slam - Allows you to slam any enemy with any wepon config, you are not slamming with a shield but rather your shoulder/body/fist. If you equip a magical item on your shoulders you can bash magical creatures such as wisps.<br>
<br>
Slam is a fixed skill, like all racial skills.<br>
<br>
Slam uses the skill bash if you have that skill trained. For instance if you train bash at lv6 you can then slam creatures while useing a 2-handed wepon but instead of useing the skill lv of slam it will use the skill lv of bash, this is usefull because slam is fixed and bash can go higher.<br>
<br>
Damage bonus : Shields cause bash to have a damage bonus - you must equip a shield in your offhand, if you slam with a shield in your offhand i am pretty sure the shield damage bonus kicks in, if you slam with a 2h it uses the regular bash skill simular to the 2-bash skill.<br>
<br>
Slam will use the same timer as bash, bash will knock out kick so you can only slam back any given time when those skills are up. (default is 6 second not hasted?)<br>
<br>
Slam/bash/kick use the same timer, so refresh at the same rate unlike discplins for instance.<br>
<br>
I heard Slam knocks out backstab for rogues, beastlords can train kick - knights an train bash, warriors can kick.. shamans cannot kick or bash so they gain the most from slam, but also cannot train in bash so the skill is almost useless to them, if beastlords wanted to slam i dont think it would be worth it as i am sure they cant train bash either so would be useing lower skill caps.<br>
<br>
Think that covers most of it.<br>
